    "summary": "Matt Wolfe presents a video titled \"9 Free AI Skills That Feel Like Cheat Codes,\" showcasing a collection of free plug‑ins and skills designed to boost the capabilities of AI coding agents such as Claude Code and Codex. The talk covers nine tools—including GStack, Stop Slop, Graphify, Understand Anything, Last 30 Days, Anthropic’s Front End Design skill, Taste Skill, ReMotion, and HyperFrames—demonstrating their installation and comparing their performance in real‑time use cases. Each skill is compatible with multiple platforms (Claude Code, Codex, Cursor, OpenClaw, Hermes, VS Code, GitHub Copilot) and the speaker provides links for live demos. The video also includes timestamps, a brief intro on skills vs plugins, and encourages viewers to engage via comments or business inquiries. Overall, it serves as a practical guide for developers seeking free ways to expand AI agent functionality.",
