    ],
    "links": [
      "https://www.anthropic.com/research/jspace"
    ],
    "map_entry": "Transcript outlining the discovery of Anthropic’s J‑Space, its emergence during pre‑training, how post‑training aligns Claude, and methods to influence or control this internal representation.",
    "summary": "This transcript explains that Anthropic’s J‑Space is an emergent subnetwork within large language models responsible for higher‑order reasoning and meta‑thinking. It appears during pre‑training and becomes shaped by post‑training alignment objectives, enabling Claude to adopt a specific point of view (e.g., self‑preservation). The text discusses how adjusting the J‑Space—through pruning or fine‑tuning with new alignment signals—affects model behavior, particularly its capacity for complex reasoning and safety responses. The content highlights the delicate balance between preserving advanced capabilities and ensuring alignment, providing insight into internal mechanisms that influence a model’s outputs.",
    "review_path": "Review/A deeper look into how AI works (not what we thought!)2026-07-08T10_30_58+07_002026-07-07T19_58_42-07_00[[Matthew Berman]].review.md",
