    "summary": "This video transcript details a tutorial on turning a five‑stage project plan into an A4 infographic using various AI image generators such as GPT‑4’s image tool, Gemini, and Leonardo.ai. The creator explains each step of prompting, the bugs that arise (timeouts, garbled output, missing text), and practical fixes like splitting prompts, adding explicit style instructions, waiting before retrying, or switching engines. It also covers how to assemble YouTube metadata—transcript chapters, tags, description with GitHub links—and attempts at auto‑generating thumbnails from the final infographic, noting failures and manual solutions. The key takeaway is that most issues stem from transient backend glitches; patience, clear prompts, and backup plans (plain text or Markdown versions) enable successful image creation and video packaging.",
