    "map_entry": "Recent AI model launches in China and Japan post-Anthropic export ban: 360 Security’s Tulongfeng and Yitianzhen for vulnerability discovery and cyber defense; Sakana AI’s Fugu conductor model. Highlights regional move to sovereign AI capabilities amid export restrictions.",
    "summary": "The document details the launch of new AI tools by Chinese firm 360 Security Technology and Japanese startup Sakana AI in response to a U.S. Commerce Department directive that barred Anthropic’s advanced models from foreign users. 360 introduced Tulongfeng for automated vulnerability detection, uncovering over 3,400 flaws, and Yitianzhen for incident response. Simultaneously, Sakana AI released Fugu, a “conductor” model that dynamically routes tasks across leading frontier engines such as GPT‑5.5, Gemini 3.5 Flash, and Claude Opus 4.8 through a single API. These developments reflect a broader regional push toward autonomous AI capabilities free from U.S. export controls, underscoring the growing importance of cybersecurity considerations in emerging model ecosystems.",
    "review_path": "Review/Perplexity.review.md",
