    "summary": "The article reports on allegations by a former KPMG audit director that senior partners used confidential Lendlease board papers and other private information to pitch for and secure lucrative audit contracts with Westpac, Dexus, Macquarie Group and others. It details the whistleblower’s claims of a cover‑up lasting over two years, the firm’s apology, the resignation of Chairman Martin Sheppard, appointment of an independent chair, commissioning of external reviews by Allens, and broader governance reforms aimed at restoring trust. The scandal is placed in context with other Big Four controversies, such as PwC’s government consulting fallout.",
