    "map_entry": "Historical overview of light speed measurement, relativity theory, and practical GPS implications.",
    "summary": "The transcript traces the evolution from ancient beliefs to modern physics: Rømer’s first indirect measurement of c, Fizeau’s laboratory experiment, Michelson‑Morley’s null test of ether, Lorentz–FitzGerald contraction, Einstein’s postulates of special relativity and E=mc², general relativity’s gravitational time dilation, and the necessity of relativistic corrections in GPS. It explains how these discoveries reshape our understanding of space, time, and energy.",
    "review_path": "Review/Upending Our Understanding of the Universe (1).review.md",
    "processed_path": "Processed/Upending Our Understanding of the Universe (1).md",
