    "summary": "The article outlines Thailand’s effort to meet a 40‑million visitor target and $3–$3.5 trillion revenue goal by attracting foreign retirees, especially post‑COVID. It examines the government’s visa reforms—extending Visa‑on‑Arrival to 60 days—and questions the reliability of tourism statistics due to past border‑run counting practices. The piece highlights the country’s advanced infrastructure for seniors (healthcare, senior‑friendly hotels), the role of Digital Tourist Visa (DTV) and Long‑Term Resident (LTR) programs in enabling long stays, and how retirees provide stable, lower‑maintenance revenue streams compared with other tourist segments.",
