    "map_entry": "Gemma 4 Desktop Exploration - concise description of the source.",
    "summary": "This document provides a step‑by‑step guide to creating an automated photo archival system that runs entirely on local hardware. It covers setting up a Llama‑3 based local LLM server, integrating a YOLOv8 vision model for object detection, reading and writing EXIF/IPTC metadata via exiftool, and orchestrating these components in a simple Python script that processes images in batches, writes titles, keywords, descriptions, renames files, and organizes them into success or review folders. The workflow demonstrates how to combine LLMs with tool‑calling and file operations for practical, offline AI projects.",
