  {
    "source_name": "Your gaming PC gets throttled by Windows 11's hidden security layer, and disabling it takes 30 seconds2026-07-07T20_35_51+07_002026-07-05T13_00_22Z[[Jasmine Mannan]].md",
    "primary_topic": "Gaming",
    "subtopics": [
      "Performance",
      "Windows 11 Security",
      "Core Isolation",
      "VBS"
    ],
    "source_language": "en",
    "reason": "The document discusses how Windows 11’s core isolation and virtualization-based security layer introduces CPU scheduling penalties that cause micro‑stutters in modern games, and explains how disabling memory integrity can improve gameplay stability.",
    "tags": [
      "gaming",
      "windows11",
      "vbs",
      "core isolation",
      "performance"
    ],
    "links": [
      "https://www.xda-developers.com/signs-your-gpu-isnt-responsible-for-fps-issues/",
      "https://www.xda-developers.com/debloating-windows-11-handheld-gaming/"
    ],
    "map_entry": "Gaming PC throttled by Windows 11’s core isolation; disabling memory integrity fixes micro‑stutters.",
    "summary": "The article explains that Windows 11, by default, activates core isolation and virtualization-based security (VBS) to sandbox kernel-mode drivers. While this protects against malware, it forces driver calls through a hypervisor layer, adding CPU latency spikes that manifest as sudden frame-time jitters in high-end gaming rigs. The author notes that disabling the memory integrity toggle under Windows Security → Device Security → Core Isolation Details eliminates these stutters—though average FPS may remain similar, low‑end frame drops drop sharply. It cautions users about sacrificing a layer of enterprise-grade security and advises gamers with secure home networks to weigh risk versus smoother gameplay.",
    "review_path": "Review/Your gaming PC gets throttled by Windows 11's hidden security layer, and disabling it takes 30 seconds2026-07-07T20_35_51+07_002026-07-05T13_00_22Z[[Jasmine Mannan]].review.md",
    "processed_path": "Processed/Your gaming PC gets throttled by Windows 11's hidden security layer, and disabling it takes 30 seconds2026-07-07T20_35_51+07_002026-07-05T13_00_22Z[[Jasmine Mannan]].md",
    "wiki_path": "Wiki/Gaming.md",
    "indexed_at": "2026-07-11 10:29:06"
  },
