    "summary": "The release of tunnel‑client v0.0.9 introduces significant infrastructure improvements for enterprises using the OpenAI API gateway. Key enhancements include optional prefixed routes for workspaces or tenants, support for client‑side mTLS authentication to secure control‑plane connections, explicit MCP session termination messages, and structured health checks that probe /healthz and /readyz endpoints. Diagnostics are enhanced with richer MCP status reporting and protected control‑plane headers. These updates aim to improve day‑2 operations, enable more robust operator monitoring, and streamline deployment in complex gateway environments.",
    "review_path": "Review/Release v0.0.9--context-conduit-topaz.review.md",
