    "map_entry": "Karpathy’s tweet outlining a personal workflow for creating LLM-based wiki knowledge bases.",
    "summary": "The post describes a process where raw source documents (articles, papers, datasets) are indexed into a raw/ folder and an LLM incrementally compiles them into a markdown wiki. The LLM maintains summaries, backlinks, and categorization. Obsidian serves as the IDE to view data. The user can query the knowledge base with complex questions; the LLM generates answers, visualizations or slide decks, which are then filed back into the wiki. Regular health checks via the LLM keep consistency. Future plans include synthetic data generation and fine‑tuning to embed knowledge in weights.",
