    "map_entry": "Weekly AI news update covering GPT‑5.6, Fable, Claude 3.5 and new multimodal features.",
    "summary": "This week’s AI news highlights the launch of OpenAI’s GPT‑5.6 with an “All‑In‑One” mode that handles text, code, images and tables in a single prompt, and its close competitor Fable which offers advanced architectural reasoning and more consistent outputs. Anthropic’s Claude 3.5 is updated to support image input/output, background web tasks and a Reflect analytics feature, providing richer multimodal interaction. Google adds video remixing via Gemini Omni in Google Photos, enabling stylized edits and imaginative memory overlays; Meta’s new Midjourney V4 and Stable Diffusion XL expand the pool of high‑resolution image generators. These releases demonstrate significant strides in multi‑modal AI models, prompting developers to explore prompt chaining, agent workflows, and architectural decision‑making powered by next‑generation LLMs.",
